'''Hip Hop High the Musical''' is a registered entertainment services brand, and '''Hip Hop High''' is a trademarked clothing products manufacturer and distributor, with operations in the United States.

==History==
Hip Hop High began in 2007 as a stage musical, with book written by Z-man and Cindy Topps, and based on a screenplay by Rodney Thornton and Z-man. The story is set in an urban city, involving a cast of characters in the racially diverse neighborhood of New York City. It premiered at the 2010 New York International Fringe festival.<ref>BWW News Desk (2011-06-01). [http://www.broadwayworld.com/wireless/read.cfm?id=162011 "'Hip Hop High - The Musical' Plays at NYC Fringe Festival, 8/13-8/29"]. ''BroadwayWorld.com''. Retrieved 2015-05-28.</ref><ref>[http://www.hvpress.net/news/125/ARTICLE/9412/2010-08-18.html âHip Hop Highâ accepted into festival (2010-08-18)"]. ''Hudson Valley Press''. Retrieved 2015-05-28.</ref>
<ref>Hoffman, Barbara (2010-08-12).[https://nypost.com/2010/08/12/fringe-in-low-places/ "Fringe in Low Places"].  Retrieved 2015-05-28.</ref>   By 2013, Rodney Thornton registered Hip Hop High the Musical as a live performance by a musical group, and Hip Hop High as a clothing and footwear brand and trademark, with the '''[[United States Patent and Trademark Office (USPTO)]]'''.<ref>[http://www.trademarkia.com/hip-hop-high-the-musical-86029459.html "HIP HOP HIGH THE MUSICAL"]. ''Trademarkia.com''. Retrieved 2015-05-28.</ref><ref>[http://www.trademarkia.com/hip-hop-high-86119675.html "HIP HOP HIGH"]. ''Trademarkia.com''. Retrieved 2015-05-28.</ref><ref>[http://www.trademarkia.com/hip-hop-high-86036007.html "HIP HOP HIGH"]. ''Trademarkia.com''. Retrieved 2015-05-28.</ref>

