=== ''Constitution'' class === Named for the [[USS Constitution|USS ''Constitution'']]. (the TOS USS ''Enterprise'' dedication plaque refers to this ship class as the "Starship Class".) {|class="wikitable" width=100% |- style="background:#e7e8ff;" ! width="110" |Name ! width="90" |Registry !Depiction |- |USS ''Constellation'' |NCC-1017 |Commanded by Commodore Matthew Decker. All of crew was killed by the Doomsday Machine except for Commodore Decker.<ref name="Doomsday">{{cite episode|title=The Doomsday Machine|episodelink=The Doomsday Machine (Star Trek: The Original Series)|series=''Star Trek''|serieslink=Star Trek: The Original Series|network=[[NBC]]|date=1967-10-20}}</ref> Used as a bomb to destroy the planet-killer. |- |USS ''Constitution'' |NCC-1700 |Lead ship of the class (previously NX-1700) |- |USS ''Defiant'' |NCC-1764 |The ship is lost in an interdimensional rift in "[[The Tholian Web]]".<ref name="Tholian Web">{{cite episode|title=The Tholian Web|episodelink=The Tholian Web|series=''Star Trek''|serieslink=Star Trek: The Original Series|network=[[NBC]]|date=1968-11-15}}</ref> Later, it is revealed she was taken by [[Mirror Universe#Enterprise|Mirror Universe]] Tholians, captured by the crew of [[Starship Enterprise#Mirror universe|ISS ''Enterprise'' (NX-01)]], and then used in the service of the [[Mirror Universe#The Original Series|Terran Empire]] in "[[In a Mirror, Darkly]]".<ref name="Mirror Darkly1">{{cite episode|title=In a Mirror, Darkly, Part I|episodelink=In a Mirror, Darkly|series=''[[Star Trek: Enterprise]]''|network=[[UPN]]|date=2005-04-22}}</ref> In ''[[Star Trek Continues]]'' (episode 8, "Still Treads the Shadow"), ''Defiant'' is duplicated during its passage through the interdimensional rift into interphasic space with only a duplicate Kirk aboard. Over the next two hundred years, it gains a sentient AI who attempts to bring it back into the prime universe. The attempt has potentially disastrous consequences and is foiled by both Kirks, the duplicate returning to interphasic space. A ''Defiant'' is mentioned, but not seen (except for a [[Wire-frame model|wireframe]] graphic) in ''[[Star Trek Discovery]]'', Season One. |- |[[Starship Enterprise#Mirror universe|ISS ''Enterprise'']] |NCC-1701 |[[Mirror Universe#The Original Series|Mirror Universe]] version of the [[USS Enterprise (NCC-1701)|USS ''Enterprise'']] in "[[Mirror, Mirror (Star Trek: The Original Series)|Mirror, Mirror]]".<ref name="Mirror">{{cite episode|title=Mirror, Mirror|episodelink=Mirror, Mirror (Star Trek: The Original Series)|series=''Star Trek''|serieslink=Star Trek: The Original Series|network=[[NBC]]|date=1967-10-06}}</ref> |- |[[USS Enterprise (NCC-1701)|USS ''Enterprise'']] |NCC-1701 |Commanded by [[Robert April]] (2245â2250), [[Christopher Pike (Star Trek)|Christopher Pike]] (2250â2265), [[James T. Kirk]] (2265-2270, 2273â2280, 2285), [[Willard Decker]] (2270-2273, ship's commander during refit up to [[V'Ger]] incident), and [[Spock]] (2280-2285, at which time ''Enterprise'' was assigned to [[Starfleet Academy]] as a training ship). Vessel's self-destruction carried out while in orbit of the [[Star Trek II: The Wrath of Khan#Plot|Genesis Planet]] to prevent ship from falling into [[Klingon]] hands.<ref name="TSFS">{{cite video|title=''[[Star Trek III: The Search for Spock]]''|date=1984-06-01|publisher=[[Paramount Pictures]]}}</ref> |- |[[USS Enterprise (NCC-1701)#Alternate reality|USS ''Enterprise'']] ([[Star Trek (film)|Kelvin Timeline]]) |NCC-1701 |Originally commanded by Christopher Pike (launched 2258), then James T. Kirk.<ref name="Trek2009" /> Destroyed by Krall in 2263.<ref name="TrekBeyond">''[[Star Trek Beyond]]''</ref> |- |USS ''Enterprise'' ([[Star Trek (film)|Kelvin Timeline]]) |NCC-1701-A |Replacement for [[USS Enterprise (NCC-1701)#Alternate reality|USS ''Enterprise'']] launched in 2263.<ref name="TrekBeyond"/> |- |USS ''Excalibur'' |NCC-1664<ref name="Encyclopedia" /> |Severely damaged and crew killed during [[