missary">{{cite episode | title = Emissary | episodelink = Emissary (Star Trek: Deep Space Nine) | series = [[Star Trek: Deep Space Nine]]}}</ref> Later located the missing Sword of Kahless. Helps rescue Sisko from the [[Jem'Hadar]].<ref name="Jem'Hadar" /> Longest surviving DS9 runabout.{{original research inline|date=June 2012}} |- |USS ''Rubicon'' |NCC-72936 |Shrunk to 6.5 centimeters.<ref>{{cite episode | title = One Little Ship | episodelink = One Little Ship | series = [[Star Trek: Deep Space Nine]]}}</ref> |- |USS ''Shenandoah'' |NCC-73024 |Taken by Dax and Worf to rescue a [[Cardassian]] informant from the Dominion.<ref>{{cite episode | title = Change of Heart | episodelink = Change of Heart (Star Trek: Deep Space Nine) | series = [[Star Trek: Deep Space Nine]]}}</ref> Severely damaged by the Jem'Hadar en route to deliver diplomatic message to [[List of recurring characters in Star Trek: Deep Space Nine#Zek|Grand Nagus Zek]].<ref name="Valiant">{{cite episode | title = Valiant | episodelink = Valiant (Star Trek: Deep Space Nine) | series = [[Star Trek: Deep Space Nine]]}}</ref> |- |USS ''Volga'' |NCC-73196 |Participates in [[botany|botanical]] survey of [[Body Parts (Star Trek: Deep Space Nine)|Torad IV]].<ref>{{cite episode | title = Body Parts | episodelink = Body Parts (Star Trek: Deep Space Nine) | series = [[Star Trek: Deep Space Nine]]}}</ref> |- |USS ''Yangtzee Kiang'' |NCC-72453 |Hijacked by [[Bajoran#Homeworld|Bajoran]] terrorist Tahna Los.<ref name="Past Prologue" /> Became the first DS9 runabout to be destroyed when it crashed on a moon in the [[Galactic quadrant (Star Trek)#Gamma Quadrant|Gamma Quadrant]].<ref>{{cite episode | title = Battle Lines | episodelink = Battle Lines (Star Trek: Deep Space Nine) | series = [[Star Trek: Deep Space Nine]]}}</ref> |- |USS ''Yolja'' |NCC-75353 |First runabout to be named after a non-Earth river. Assigned to Deep Space 9. Appeared in ''Worlds of Star Trek: Deep Space Nine'', Volume Three - ''The Dominion: Oly