{{Infobox person | name = Riley Schillaci | image = | caption = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1982|12|22}} | birth_place = [[Rochester, New York|Rochester]], New York, United States | nationality = American | known_for = ''[[America's Got Talent]]'' contestant, season 6. ''[[Ripley's Believe It or Not]]'' | occupation = [[performance artist]] ([[Sword swallowing|sword swallower]], fire artist) | years_active = 2007 â present | website = [http://www.oddgirl.net/ oddgirl.net] }}
'''Riley Schillaci''' (born December 22, 1982) is an American [[performance artist]], specializing in [[sword swallowing]] as one of few professional female sword swallowers in the world.<ref name="Siegel">{{cite news|page=D1 |newspaper= [[The Morning Call]] |date=February 24, 2012|section=Life |title=Cutting-Edge Entertainment. Allentown woman is one of few professional female sword swallowers in the world |author=Steve Siegel|accessdate=August 28, 2012|url=http://articles.mcall.com/2012-02-24/entertainment/mc-sword-swallower-allentown-20120224_1_sword-swallowers-association-international-real-sword-allentown-woman}}</ref>
==Early life and inception of career== Riley Schillaci was born on December 22, 1982, in [[Rochester, New York]]. In her childhood, she observed a relative who swallowed forks and knives and stuck licorice up his nose, only to have it reemerge through his mouth. At around 14, Schillaci decided to try swallowing objects because she believed the talent was genetic. She moved on to swallowing drum sticks and glow sticks,<ref name="Uthe">{{cite news|page=23|newspaper=Webster Post|date=January 13, 2008|section=Sundayam|title=Don't try this at home, boys and girls. Sword swallowing 'extremely difficult and dangerous'|author=Tori Uthe|accessdate=August 28, 2012|url=http://www.mpnnow.com/entertainment/x9495918|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120723042657/http://www.mpnnow.com/entertainment/x9495918|archivedate=July 23, 2012|df=}}</ref> and by post-college she swallowed swords.<ref name="Siegel"/> She swallowed her first sword ({{convert|17|in|cm}}) in a sword store.<ref name="Zagofsky"/> Her second sword ({{convert|36|in|cm}}) was ordered by mail. Her parents held it while she "eased up into it ... 'until it just barely hit the bottom of my stomach'". She cut off the protruding part, making the sword {{convert|19|in|cm}}. Although her parents wanted her to be a singer, they supported her as a sword swallower by attending some of her performances.<ref name="Siegel"/>
==Career==
===Performance=== Schillaci was a featured season 6 contestant on ''[[America's Got Talent]]'' but was rejected by the judges because she did not smile enough.<ref name="Siegel"/> One of fewer than 20 female sword swallowers in the world,<ref name="Zagofsky">{{cite news|page= |newspaper= [[Erie Times-News]] |date= June 12, 2010|section= |title= Hard economic times led couple to ... gulp ... a strange profession|author= Al Zagofsky|accessdate=August 28, 2012|url=http://www.tnonline.com/2010/jun/12/sharpening-their-skills}}</ref> she worked with ''[[Ripley's Believe It or Not!]]''<ref name="Siegel"/> and is a member of the Sword Swallowers Association International.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.swordswallow.com/performers.php |title=Actively Performing Professional Sword Swallowers|author=[[Dan Meyer (performer)|Dan Meyer]] |date=2011 |work=Sword Swallowers Association International |accessdate=September 2, 2012}}</ref> She uses [[rum]] to disinfect her sword before swallowing it.<ref name="Voorhees">{{cite news|page= |newspaper= [[YNN Rochester]] |date=February 28, 2008|section= |title=Her Hobby's Hard To Swallow|author=Seth Voorhees |accessdate=August 28, 2012|url=http://rochester.ynn.com/content/358731/her-hobby-s-hard-to-swallow/}}</ref> Schillaci said that her throat becomes faintly sore after sword swallowing a few times per week.<ref name="Uthe"/>
Besides sword swallowing, her acts include fire eating, fire breathing, human blockhead, human pincushion, and bed of nails.<ref name="Siegel"/> She calls her overall act "Odd Girl".<ref>{{cite news|page= |newspaper= [[WPVI-TV]] |date=April 1, 2012|section=|title=Allentown woman makes a living swallowing swords |author=Walter Perez|accessdate=August 28, 2012 |url=http://abclocal.go.com/wpvi/story?section=news/local&id=8603309}}</ref>
===Other=== Having earned a degree in sociology and health science, Schillaci has worked in factories, [[special education]], child care, web development, and in administration.<ref name="Zagofsky"/> Her hobbies include writing and playing music.<ref name="Uthe"/>
